---
Warlocks evolved from cipher shadow-workers who discovered resonance in the dark spaces between their strikes — a pick-lock that opens not through mechanical manipulation but through the lock's internal state yielding, a pocket emptied through a moment in which the target's awareness is simply elsewhere. Those who pursued this sense deliberately found shadow compacts: working relationships with entities of poorly understood nature that the tradition describes variously as spirits, embodied principles of entropy, or Black Sun Shard fragments that have achieved autonomous agency outside the Great Pyramid's containment. The tradition avoids the last description because its implications are uncomfortable: if compact counterparties are Shard fragments, then the Warlock tradition's power source is the same cosmic threat the cleric tradition has spent millennia containing. Each practitioner's compact is a private particular agreement — no standardized structure exists, which is why the tradition was never formally codified. The hex craft organized around the art of undoing attacks through undermining systems targets depend on: protection wards becoming unreliable, combat reflexes slowing at specific moments, stable footing and concentration degrading. Hex specialization varies by compact: entropy hexes accelerate natural degradation; shadow hexes interfere with target perceptual and cognitive access; binding hexes constrain target actions at specific moments. The tradition's one universally consistent doctrinal claim is that every hex carries a price — the compact is a working relationship, not a free power source, and the entity receives something from every application. Price form varies: attention cost (entity awareness accumulating knowledge of the practitioner), resonance debt (each application deepens the compact in ways that make disengagement harder), or concrete extraction (specific memories, emotional states, or physical capacity). The Nightblade adept synthesis combines full Assassin positioning methodology with full Warlock compact practice.

