Umbral orientation toward absence positions practitioners naturally in the compact-seeking space — shadow compact entities operate in a register Umbral heritage accesses more naturally than human cipher-tradition practitioners. Where a human cipher practitioner encounters compact resonance as unexpected disruption of physical outcomes, Umbral's baseline relationship to shadow creates a lower threshold for compact perception. Umbral Warlocks' Indigo jurisdiction filing describes a compact origin less anomalous than human practitioners' — the entity is not a deviation from expected phenomena but a contact established through Umbral's native perceptual access. The Magistracy's concern remains the attention-cost dimension regardless of initial compact establishment. The Neon Covenant mythology creates framing challenges for Umbral Warlocks — a practitioner drawing power from absence-affiliated entities must frame that relationship carefully in a city whose founding mythology emphasizes collective covenant.

