Midgaard's Compact Practice Provisions were developed with human cipher-tradition Warlocks as the primary model, creating documentation gaps for Umbral practitioners whose compact origin does not fit the expected cipher-resonance-discovery narrative. The Registry's entity nature documentation requirement — describe the compact counterparty in terms the practitioner understands it — produces very different filings from Umbral practitioners who understand their compact counterparty as a natural extension of their racial heritage rather than as a distinct entity encountered through resonance discovery. Continuity faction assessors sometimes challenge the absence of the resonance discovery narrative as evidence of incomplete filing, which Umbral practitioners contest as a framework-inappropriate requirement. The Reckoning faction has noted that the Compact Practice Provisions' implicit assumption that all compacts originate through the cipher-resonance pattern is itself a form of institutional framework capture.

