Rivennid experience the world as network — connective tissue, flow paths, and distribution nodes. Warlock hex craft, framed as art of undoing, attacks the network connections that targets depend on: protection ward networks, reflex-response networks, environmental perception networks. A Rivennid Warlock approaches hex application with native awareness of which network connections are structural (removal produces cascade failure) versus redundant (removal produces degraded function but not failure). This produces more precise hex applications than practitioners working from the entropy-doctrine framing — the Rivennid's network topology perception identifies specific connection nodes whose disruption produces the most efficient degradation. Wall Command assessors note that Rivennid Warlocks produce operational outcomes with less collateral effect than equivalent hex applications from human practitioners, because network precision avoids disrupting connections the target shares with adjacent systems.
